Package variationPointsVisualization

package variationPointsVisualization
  • Class
    Description
    AnnotationExtensionMarker
    Manages creations and recognitions of system annotations for negative variability
    AnnotationExtensionMarker.SystemAnnotationType
    Enumeration with different system negative variability annotation types -descriptive names that are used in final SPL are associated to them
    DifferentAnnotationTypesOnTheSameVariationPoint
    Exception capturing different annotation types on the same variation point -for example annotation for class cannot be inserted in place where method annotation is placed
    DuplicatedAnnotation
    Exception capturing duplicated annotation that is found on AST
    NegativeVariabilityAnnotationAggregator
    Aggregator of negative variability annotation
    NegativeVariabilityAnnotationElement
    Negative variation point annotation representation
    NegativeVariabilityDecoratorConsistenceVerifier
    Verify if variation point belongs to negative variability and its consistency -checks if annotation is user annotation or system annotation and thus belongs to negative variation point annotations -consistency is verified according pre-configured settings for example if user annotation is used then no system annotations are used in one code fragment
    ParameterExtensionMarker
    Manages declaration of variable extensions
    VariationPointsWithVariablesMarker
    Manages creation of positive variation point markers in form of variables
    VariationPointsWithVariablesMarker.DeclarationTypes
    Enumeration of all available declaration types in JavaScript/TypeScript
